 Pierre and Miquelon":"Saint Pierre and Miquelon","Perth, Perthshire, Scotland, United Kingdom":"Perth, Perthshire, Scotland, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Menteith","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Scottish: habitational name from the earldom and province of <i>Menteith</i> in Perthshire, named in Gaelic as ‘hill pasture (above) the Teith’, from <i>monadh</i> ‘hill pasture’ + <i>Teith</i>, a river name of obscure origin. This name was introduced to Ulster at the time of the Plantation in the 17th century, where it is now quite numerous in certain areas, particularly Tyrone."],"variants":[{"name":"Montooth","meanings":["Probably an altered form of Scottish   Monteith  ."]},{"name":"Mantooth","meanings":["Probably an altered form of Scottish   Monteith   or<b>Mantach</b>, a nickname from Gaelic <i>manntach</i> ‘stammering’(also ‘toothless’ in Irish), of which one early Welsh recorded form is<i>Mantath</i>."]},{"name":"Montierth","meanings":["Scottish: variant of   Monteith  ."]},{"name":"Montieth","meanings":["Scottish (Lanarkshire): variant of   Monteith   This form of the surname is rare in Britain."]}]},{"name":"Mary","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["From Hebrew.  See  <b>Maria</b>   and   <b>Mary</b> ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Mary Menteith was born about 1185, in Perthshire, Scotland, United Kingdom. She married Muireadhach II Menteith The Younger, Earl of Menteith about 1200. They were the parents of at least 1 son and 2 daughters. She died in 1272, in Saint Pierre and Miquelon, at the age of 88."},"et":{"about 1185–1272":"umbes 1185–1272","1170–1234":"1170–1234","1195–1272":"1195–1272","1225–1286":"1225–1286","1230–Male":"1230–Surnud","1185–1272":"1185–1272","1225":"1225","Abt 1200":"umbes 1200","1234":"1234","1286":"1286","1230":"1230","Abt 1225":"umbes 1225","1185":"1185","1195":